DOM-based XSS — flag any of:
- document.write() with user input
- innerHTML / outerHTML assignment from untrusted data
- location.href / location.hash used unsanitized
- eval() on URL parameters or query strings
- jQuery .html(), .append() with untrusted data
- window.location, document.referrer used in DOM

Stored XSS — flag any of:
- User input saved to DB then rendered without encoding
- Template rendering without escaping
- {{ variable }} vs escaped {{% %}} in templates

Missing XSS protections — flag if absent:
- Content-Security-Policy header
- X-XSS-Protection header
- Output encoding before render
- DOMPurify or equivalent sanitization library

